  "prompt": "What are the Japanese names that mean \"dragon\"?",
  "response": "In Japanese culture, dragons hold significant symbolic meaning, often associated with strength, wisdom, and good fortune. Here are several Japanese names that include the kanji character for \"dragon,\" which is \"\u7adc\" or \"\u9f8d\":\n\n### Boys' Names:\n1. **Tatsu (\u30bf\u30c4 or \u7adc)**\n   - Directly means \"dragon.\"\n   \n2. **Ry\u016b (\u30ea\u30e5\u30a6 or \u7adc)**\n   - Another common reading of the kanji for \"dragon.\"\n\n3. **Ry\u016bji (\u30ea\u30e5\u30a6\u30b8 or \u7adc\u4e8c)**\n   - \"Ry\u016b\" (dragon) combined with \"ji\" (second son).\n\n4. **Ry\u016btar\u014d (\u30ea\u30e5\u30a6\u30bf\u30ed\u30a6 or \u7adc\u592a\u90ce)**\n   - \"Ry\u016b\" (dragon) combined with \"tar\u014d,\" a common ending for boys' names, meaning \"eldest son.\"\n\n5. **Tatsuya (\u30bf\u30c4\u30e4 or \u7adc\u4e5f)**\n   - \"Tatsu\" (dragon) combined with \"ya,\" a common ending for boys' names.\n\n### Girls' Names:\n1. **Ry\u016bko (\u30ea\u30e5\u30a6\u30b3 or \u7adc\u5b50)**\n   - \"Ry\u016b\" (dragon) combined with \"ko,\" a common ending for girls' names, meaning \"child\" or \"girl.\"\n\n2. **Tatsuki (\u30bf\u30c4\u30ad or \u7adc\u59eb)**\n   - \"Tatsu\" (dragon) combined with \"ki,\" meaning \"princess.\"\n\n3. **Ry\u016bna (\u30ea\u30e5\u30a6\u30ca or \u7adc\u5948)**\n   - \"Ry\u016b\" (dragon) combined with \"na,\" a common feminine name ending.\n\n4. **Tatsue (\u30bf\u30c4\u30a8 or \u7adc\u6075)**\n   - \"Tatsu\" (dragon) combined with \"e,\" meaning \"blessing\" or \"grace.\"\n\n5. **Ry\u016bmi (\u30ea\u30e5\u30a6\u30df or \u7adc\u7f8e)**\n   - \"Ry\u016b\" (dragon) combined with \"mi,\" meaning \"beauty.\"\n\nThese names can be used to symbolize the admirable qualities associated with dragons in Japanese folklore and mythology.",
